import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(data=data, orient='h', palette='Set2', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values for u and v?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(['u', 'v'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    correlation_matrix = data.corr()
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap="coolwarm")
    plt.title("Is there any correlation between u and v?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue', label='u distribution')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of u?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
